   <pb facs="137"/>
   <head>Advertissement au Lecteur.</head>
   <opener>
      <salute>Generous READER,</salute>
   </opener>
   <p>'TWas upon occasion of the last <hi>Summer's</hi> sad ef<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>fects generally over all <hi>England,</hi> and some ressent<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>ments of mine owne; when the Reading and Copying <hi>English</hi> this Authour's <hi>French</hi> Originall, seasona<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>bly engaged my thoughts, and <hi>Pen.</hi> I thinke al's not forgotten yet: But in a longer intervall, and indeed <hi>alwayes,</hi> there ought still to bee a deepe apprehension of our <hi>Mortality.</hi> This our <hi>AUTHOR</hi> inculcates to us in Notions quicke and pertinent, though in some historicall allusions he may a little o're-trust his Me<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>mory.</p>
   <closer>
      <salute>Valebis.</salute>
      <signed>THO. CARY.</signed>
   </closer>
   <epigraph>
      <q>—Laudatus abundè Non fastiditus—</q>
   </epigraph>
